<item>
            <title>[JCR-2518] Make ItemIds more stable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2518</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>The ItemIds returned by spi2dav are currently not stable in the sense that they are sometimes uuid based and sometimes not: If a node is referenceable some of its properties will receive fully path based ids while others will receive ids based on the uuid of its parent node. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The efficiency of caching introduced with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2498&quot; title=&quot;Implement caching mechanism for ItemInfo batches&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JCR-2498&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; depends on stable ids. I therefore suggest to improve spi2dav such that property ids are always uuid based if the parent&amp;#39;s node has a uuid. </description>
